      <h1>Online Services Guidelines</h1>
      <img alt="login" src="../../images/login.jpg" class="img_style_right">
      <p>The Govt. of Bihar has launched the e-Municipality software which would reach out to the citizens and enable them to avail services on fingertips. This initiative would help deliver citizen services in a transparent, effective and efficient manner.</p>
      <p>Citizens can avail various anytime, anywhere services through various modes of delivery:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Citizen Facilitation Center (CFC) </li>
        <li>Cyber Cafe  - depending upon ULB's tie ups with such cyber cafe</li>
        <li>Sitting at home through internet</li>
        <li>Payments can be made via Payment gateway using Debit/ Credit cards or by generating Challan and making payments in Banks/Municipalities.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>It provides municipal services through online/Single Window service delivery channel and ensures accessible, convenient, transparent and timely delivery of services.</p>
      <p>In order to avail various online services, user must login with the appropriate login credentials.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Citizen Services Login :</strong> The Citizen will have to register them and then login to access the online services. </li>
        <li><strong>Agency Login :</strong> Agency login enables agencies like Hospitals, Cyber cafe, architects, builders, advocates, etc to register themselves on the ULB portal and then login to access the online services.</li>
        <li><strong>Department Login :</strong> Department login is provided to the employee of the Municipal Corporation to authorize and process the service requests, collect payments, etc.</li>
      </ul>
  </section> 
  
  
