   <h1>RTI</h1>
<p>Under the RTI section, Citizens can avail the following services:</p>					

    <ul>
    	<li>RTI Application Entry</li>
    	<li>First Appeal Entry</li>
    </ul>
    
<h3>Process Flow:</h3>    
    
    <ul>
    	<li>Citizen files an RTI application. </li>
    	<li>Pay the prescribed fees.If Citizen is not Below Poverty Line, fees have to be paid. It can be paideither Online (Credit Card/Debit Card/Net Banking) or Offline (via Challan at ULB or at Bank).</li>
    	<li>PIO (Public Information Officer) decides whether to accept or reject the application.
        	<ul>
            	<li>If Accepted:PIO generates LOI (Letter of Intimation) which contains declaration of the charges that Citizen needs to pay to obtain the desired information.</li>
            	<li>If Rejected:PIO provides Rejection letter to the Citizen with proper reason.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    	<li>Citizen can raise First Appeal if the information is incomplete, unsatisfactory or rejected by the PIO. The application will be automatically sent to First Appellate Authority.</li>
    	<li>Citizen's First Appeal is either Accepted or Rejected by the Appellant Committee.</li>
    	<li>If the First Appeal is accepted, Appointment Details for the hearing are provided.</li>
    	<li>If the result is in favor of the Citizen, then RTI application is again forwarded to the PIO to provide the required information else the Citizen is informed.</li>
    </ul>
    
    
<h2>Charges:</h2> 
<ul>
	<li>RTI Application Charges would be Rs. 10. This charge is not applicable if applicant is BPL (Below Poverty Line).</li>
	<li>Charges for providing information in different media:
        <ul>
            <li>For Letter - Rs 2 per page</li>
            <li>For CD - Rs 50 per disc</li>
        </ul>   
    </li>
</ul> 
  </section> 
  
